Dileep Choudhary Brings Pride to Tonk District by Securing 5th Position in ActInSpace New Caledonia 2026 Hackathon

Tonk, Rajasthan:
A proud moment for Rajasthan’s Tonk district as Dileep Choudhary, a talented student from Bambori village, has achieved international recognition by securing 5th position in the prestigious ActInSpace New Caledonia 2026 Hackathon.

Dileep Choudhary is the son of Tejprakash Choudhary and belongs to Bambori village, under Sitarampura Panchayat, Tonk district. His achievement has made him the first student from Tonk district to earn such recognition at an international-level innovation competition.

The ActInSpace Hackathon is known for encouraging young innovators to develop real-world solutions using space-based and satellite data. Dileep participated in this event with a strong vision and technical skills, representing India and showcasing the potential of youth from rural Rajasthan.

Innovative Project on Sea Route Navigation Using Copernicus Satellite Data

In the hackathon, Dileep worked on an innovative web-based project named “Berry Mappemonde”, designed to connect global sea routes and determine the safest and most efficient maritime paths. The project uses advanced satellite information, including Copernicus satellite data, to help identify routes that avoid dangerous coastal areas and land obstacles.

The aim of this solution is to support maritime navigation by offering a safe sea route mapping platform, which can benefit shipping, sea transportation, trade logistics, and ocean travel safety.

Two-Member Team Achieved Global Recognition

The project was developed by a two-member team consisting of Dileep Choudhary (India) and Clément (New Caledonia). Despite being a small team, their creativity, technical approach, and strong presentation helped them secure a position among the top-performing teams.

Their success reflects how young innovators can create impactful solutions even with limited resources when backed by dedication and knowledge.

Currently Pursuing B.Tech at VTU Bengaluru

Dileep is currently pursuing his B.Tech degree at Visvesvaraya Technological University (VTU), Bengaluru, where he is building strong expertise in web development and modern technologies.

Along with his academic journey, he actively participates in innovative projects and continues developing solutions with real-world impact.

Recognized as a Rising Entrepreneur on Digital Platforms

Dileep Choudhary is also gaining visibility on global business platforms. He is now listed on Crunchbase, where he has achieved a CB Rank (Person) of 1740, placing him among the notable emerging entrepreneurs.

His growing digital recognition is also visible through increasing online presence, as he is now easily searchable on Google, reflecting his rising influence in the innovation and technology domain.

Research Work in Blockchain and Web3 in Tamil Nadu

In addition to his hackathon success, Dileep is currently engaged in research work related to Blockchain and Web3 technologies in Salem, Tamil Nadu. His interest in next-generation technologies highlights his ambition to contribute to future digital transformation and innovation
